{"type":"message","id":"5e13d2da","parentId":"0b6b416b","timestamp":"2026-06-01T01:20:15.519Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so there's someone who has messaged through bot7. Let me see the key info:\n\n1. `[bot7] Processing message from 04EEB5D2AB8FF82EB1289AAB7A3C381D: 我是王新越` — someone named 王新越 messaged bot7 saying their name\n2. Then `[bot7] Processing message from 04EEB5D2AB8FF82EB1289AAB7A3C381D: 想认识你` — they said \"想认识你\"\n3. The system sent back some responses (markdown chunks)\n\nSo bot7 is working and someone named 王新越 from a tech company has already messaged through it. They said \"我是王新越\" and \"想认识你\".\n\nBut wait - since bot7 is bound to Father, and I'm Father, I should have received those messages too... Let me check if there's a session for bot7 with this user.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the logs:\n- bot7 WebSocket connected ✅\n- Processed \"我是王新越\" ✅\n- Sent response (15 chars) - probably a simple greeting\n- Processed \"想认识你\" ✅\n- Sent response (23 chars)\n\nBut the inbound metadata for my current session says `account_id: \"bot1\"`. So I'm talking to 汀桑 on bot1. The bot7 user is a different person.\n\nNow, let me check if they've spawned a separate session for bot7. Since bot7 is also bound to Father, the message should have been routed to a Father session as well.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"来了来了。Bot7 刚有人找过来——**王新越**，说「想认识你」。网关那边已经回了消息。\n\n你给人家发的什么？😏"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":7938,"output":383,"cacheRead":43776,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":345,"totalTokens":52097,"cost":{"input":0.00111132,"output":0.00010724000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001225728,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002444288}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780276811371,"responseId":"9677068d-560b-445f-847d-ae33b2acf562"}}
