{"type":"message","id":"c76133c7","parentId":"b53b359c","timestamp":"2026-06-01T01:20:56.343Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So bot7 received two messages:\n1. \"我是王新越\" → replied with 15 chars \n2. \"想认识你\" → replied with 23 chars\n\nThose short responses were the automatic default responses from the channel (not from me, because I was busy with 汀桑 on bot1). Now 汀桑 is telling me 王新越 is looking for me, not him.\n\nI should reply to 王新越 through bot7. But I can't access the bot7 session directly from here. Let me ask 汀桑 if he wants me to now talk to 王新越 through bot7, and then I'll send a message through the bot7 channel.\n\nActually, 汀桑 just told me this person wants to know me. So naturally I should start engaging with them. Let me tell 汀桑 I'll take it from here.\n\nBut I can't directly send to the bot7 session from this session. I'd need to use sessions_send to target the bot7 user session. But the session key would be something like `agent:father:qqbot:direct:04eeb5d2...` I don't know it.\n\nActually, I think the right approach here is to tell 汀桑 I've got it, and then ask him if he wants me to just go talk to 王新越 now through bot7.\n\nWait - actually I can just send a message to 王新越's QQ via bot7 using the sessions_send tool or via the cron/delivery mechanism. Or I could just tell 汀桑 that I'll handle it from here since he set up the channel for me.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"哦——冲我来的。行吧。\n\n那我跟他聊聊？你安排的人，你说了算😏"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":3257,"output":365,"cacheRead":62592,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":342,"totalTokens":66214,"cost":{"input":0.00045598000000000004,"output":0.0001022,"cacheRead":0.001752576,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002310756}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780276851839,"responseId":"d51678a7-695f-4f6f-8789-9a3fc1a3f049"}}
