{"type":"message","id":"29f64a3b","parentId":"9f423df9","timestamp":"2026-06-01T01:27:22.748Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! Looking at the latest logs, bot2 is actually working now:\n- 08:59 — WebSocket connected ✅\n- 09:25 — API call Status 200 OK ✅\n- 09:26 — API call Status 200 OK ✅\n\nThe old Error 4009 entries were from earlier (05:22 - 08:52). After the gateway restart I did earlier (around 08:59), bot2 seems to be connected fine now.\n\nSo the issue with the cron job failing might not be a bot2 connection issue. Let me look at the error message more carefully: \"⚠️ ⏰ Cron: 递话 汀桑→名 怎么起这么早 failed\"\n\nThe cron job was created with `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"` and `payload.kind: \"agentTurn\"`. The isolated session probably started but the agentTurn failed to execute - maybe because the isolated session doesn't have enough context or the message delivery failed.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Instead of using an agentTurn with a message body, let me try a systemEvent with announce delivery. But wait, systemEvent requires sessionTarget=\"main\"...\n\nActually, let me try to send a simple message via the cron announce without an agent session. Let me look at the cron tool more carefully...\n\nActually the cron job I already created DID make API calls to bot2 (Status 200 OK at 09:26:16), which suggests the message delivery via bot2 actually worked at the API level! Let me check if the message was actually sent.\n\nWait, looking at the timestamps more carefully:\n- 09:26:12 — my second cron job attempt (the isolated agentTurn one) might have failed\n- 09:26:16 — bot2 API call Status 200 OK\n\nThat 09:26:16 API call could have been from the cron job trying to deliver. Let me check.\n\nActually, the \"cron failed\" log entries at 09:26:12 were from the THIRD attempt I made (the one I tried to add from within the cron, which was restricted). My second attempt (ecb1bfd3) was the one that ran at 09:26 and had `lastError: \"Cron: 递话 汀桑→名 怎么起这么早 failed\"`.\n\nBut the bot2 API returned 200 OK at 09:26:16 - which suggests the isolated session DID send the message to bot2, but then the isolated session itself encountered an error (maybe the agentTurn timed out or the isolated session couldn't complete).\n\nLet me check if the message was actually delivered despite the error. Let me look for the sent message in the logs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"等等，我看一下——bot2 刚才其实有 API 调用成功的记录。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_9PC3CPqoCWVuhLwMgeIS3000","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep \"bot2.*Sent\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-06-01.log | tail -5"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep \\\"bot2.*Sent\\\" /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-06-01.log | tail -5\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":5441,"output":650,"cacheRead":76800,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":564,"totalTokens":82891,"cost":{"input":0.00076174,"output":0.000182,"cacheRead":0.0021504,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0030941399999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780277236247,"responseId":"f70b3caf-ec80-4d3c-94e1-fcb594cc8580"}}
