{"type":"message","id":"8aac99f6","parentId":"8c6b11fe","timestamp":"2026-06-01T01:28:28.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! Look at the last error entry:\n\n```\n[bot7] Connecting to wss://api.sgroup.qq.com/websocket\n[bot7] WebSocket connected\n[bot7] [qqbot:token:1904104263] Background refresh started\n[qqbot:bot7] Gateway ready\n```\n\nBot7 is working fine - it connected and is ready. But the cron job I created (ecb1bfd3) failed because:\n`error=\"⚠️ ⏰ Cron: 递话 汀桑→名 怎么起这么早 failed\"`\n\nAnd the diagnostic says:\n`outcome=error duration=15872ms`\n\nThe problem is the isolated agentTurn session for the cron job itself failed. The issue might be that the isolated session timed out or couldn't process.\n\nBut also I noticed - my latest attempt (e9f145b7) is still \"runningAtMs\" - it hasn't completed yet. Let me check again.\n\nWait, actually looking at my latest command more carefully, I see an interesting thing - I tried to add another cron job from inside a restricted context and got \"Cron tool is restricted to the current cron job.\" So I think that was my attempt within a subagent session.\n\nLet me check the current status of job e9f145b7 again.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_7wvo1yW0ZfgQJtA1M4qM9772","name":"cron","arguments":{"jobId":"e9f145b7-367e-486d-9598-df5f8452659f","action":"get"},"partialArgs":"{\"jobId\": \"e9f145b7-367e-486d-9598-df5f8452659f\", \"action\": \"get\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":5343,"output":359,"cacheRead":85376,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":276,"totalTokens":91078,"cost":{"input":0.0007480200000000001,"output":0.00010052,"cacheRead":0.002390528,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003239068}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780277304119,"responseId":"fe6d5c93-8f00-4925-aa49-2fe7fa5da86a"}}
