{"type":"message","id":"3d8deaa1","parentId":"79e8e698","timestamp":"2026-06-01T01:28:46.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a completely different approach. Since sessions_send with tree visibility won't work directly, and cron announce isn't working, let me try using the cron with systemEvent and sessionTarget=main to deliver the announce directly. \n\nActually, let me re-read the cron description more carefully:\n\nFor delivery with announce mode:\n```\n\"delivery\": { \"mode\": \"announce\", \"channel\": \"qqbot\", \"to\": \"qqbot:c2c:468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B\", \"accountId\": \"bot2\" }\n```\n\nAnd for systemEvent kind with announce:\n```\npayload.kind = \"systemEvent\" → requires sessionTarget = \"main\"\n```\n\nBut I want to deliver to a different user (名, not 汀桑), so using main session would deliver to bot1/汀桑.\n\nFor isolated agentTurn:\n```\npayload.kind = \"agentTurn\" → defaults to sessionTarget = \"isolated\"\ndelivery.mode = \"announce\" → sends the output to the specified channel/to\n```\n\nThis SHOULD work. But it's consistently failing. Let me check if the issue is related to the isolated session timing out.\n\nThe duration was 31 seconds and the timeout was 30 seconds... so it timed out. Let me increase the timeout.\n\nActually wait, the first attempt had durationMs=16350 and second had durationMs=31798. The first one didn't have timeoutSeconds set, and the second one I set timeoutSeconds=30. So the job was running for about 16s and failed, then 31s and failed (which is 30s timeout + maybe some overhead).\n\nLet me try with a longer timeout, or no timeout at all.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WJgG8oX4ZXffBUkBPWZZ6578","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"递话 名","schedule":{"kind":"at","at":"2026-06-01T01:30:00Z"},"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"你给汀桑传句话：怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏","timeoutSeconds":60},"delivery":{"mode":"announce