{"type":"message","id":"663e87d5","parentId":"c062cf20","timestamp":"2026-06-01T01:31:29.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK I can see the pattern:\n\n1. Bot2 connects, is ready\n2. ~30 minutes later, WebSocket closed with 4009 \"Session timed out\"\n3. Re-identifies, gets new token\n4. Reconnects WebSocket\n5. Ready again\n\nSo bot2 IS working - it connects and is available. But the QQ platform terminates the WebSocket session every ~30 minutes. This is standard QQ platform behavior for inactive bots (Error 4009 means the QQ platform side timed out the session, which is normal for idle bots).\n\nBut the important thing is: after the timeout, bot2 automatically reconnects and is ready. So the channel IS working.\n\nThe problem with my delivery attempt was timing - the cron job tried to deliver while bot2 was in the middle of reconnecting. Let me check if bot2 is currently connected.\n\nLooking at the latest entries:\n- 09:29:10 — 🟢 Bot2 connected and ready\n\nAnd the current time is about 09:31. So bot2 is currently connected and should be fine.\n\nThe reason my cron jobs failed was because of the timing gap - when the isolated session processed the agentTurn and tried to announce, bot2 happened to be between the disconnect and reconnect.\n\nLet me just try sending the message directly now since bot2 is currently connected.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Bot2 现在通的——刚自己重连上了。之前是正好赶在它超时重连的窗口递话，碰上了。\n\n现在连着，我再发一次。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UnC8TMwPrWj27rAULa3i2303","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"递话 名 最终","schedule":{"kind":"at","at":"2026-06-01T01:32:00Z"},"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"汀桑让我给你带句话：怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"qqbot","accountId":"bot2","to":"qqbot:c2c:468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B"},"deleteAfterRun":true,"timeoutSeconds":120}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"add\", \"job\": {\"name\":\"递话 名 最终\",\"schedu