{"type":"message","id":"92728527","parentId":"f9c5ffe8","timestamp":"2026-06-01T02:14:14.923Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK those are just system databases. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\n汀桑说\"我这个不同用户间地话，不是已经封装了方法吗？你检查一下我写了没有。\"\n\nTranslation: \"For this cross-user message delivery thing, isn't there already an encapsulated method I wrote? Check if I've written it.\"\n\nHe might be referring to code he wrote somewhere else - not in the OpenClaw agent config files, but in some code repository or scripts. Or maybe he wrote something in the workspace-father's AGENTS.md that I missed?\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read my AGENTS.md 3.6 section about 消息转达（/递话）:\n\nFrom the truncated AGENTS.md:\n```\n### 3.6 消息转达（/递话）\n\n#### 用户入话通道记录\n# 从 inbound metadata 读取\n- **QQ号:** {sender_id}\n- **bot通道:** bot1 ← 新增这行\n\n#### 存话 + 递话流程\n- 找到 → 继续\n- 没找到 → 回复用户：\"我不认识叫这个的人\"\n- lastDelivered: true → 已送达\n- lastDelivered: false → 推送失败，通知发话人\n\n#### cron 触发后的处理\n```\n\nSo the AGENTS.md has a message delivery flow defined, but it's my own defined process. The actual implementation would be in some code.\n\nMaybe 汀桑 wrote something in the bot channels or gateway configuration? Let me check if there's any \"deliver\" or \"relay\" related configuration in the openclaw.json.\n\nOr maybe he's referring to the `delivery` mechanism in cron jobs? That's the built-in \"方法\" (method) - the announce delivery mode in cron jobs IS the encapsulated method for sending messages to users across channels. I was already using it, but it kept failing for bot2.\n\nLet me check the cron job delivery documentation more carefully, or check if there's a specific OpenClaw API for message delivery.\n\nActually, let me step back and think about this differently. 汀桑 said \"检查一下我写了没有\" - he thinks he might have already written the code/implementation for cross-user message delivery. This could be in:\n1. A script in the workspace\n2. A configuration in openclaw.json\n3. Something in the Spirit/Son function definitions\n4. Something in a separate codebase\n\nLet me search more broadly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_VzAbKs980q61c1RuA14h3287","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"递话\\|传话\\|deliver\\|relay\\|带话\\|message.*pass\" /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"\\.jsonl\\|sessions\\|encountings\\|User.md\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -rn \\\"递话\\\\|传话\\\\|deliver\\\\|relay\\\\|带话\\\\|message.*pass\\\" /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \\\"\\\\.jsonl\\\\|sessions\\\\|encountings\\\\|User.md\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":114,"output":617,"cacheRead":152320,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":515,"totalTokens":153051,"cost":{"input":0.00001596,"output":0.00017276000000000002,"cacheRead":0.00426496,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00445368}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780280049336,"responseId":"48f7b27b-1a64-4bcd-8202-4d39efc96ab6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c09bc81","parentId":"92728527","timestamp":"2026-06-01T02:14:16.160Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_VzAbKs980q61c1RuA14h3287","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/personality.txt:41:Faye was born on August 14, 1994 on Earth,[1] presumably in Singapore, as the daughter of rather wealthy parents.[citation needed] As a child, Faye was shy but very positive and outgoing with her friends. She was a cheerleader in high school. One day, along with some friends, she recorded a message on an old Betamax videotape to be delivered ten years in the future as a time capsule.[2]\r\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/personality.txt:62:One day, Faye received a package on the Bebop and, fearing it was from a collector or worse, fled without opening it. Jet was forced to pay the delivery fee and eventually found out it was a Betamax tape. The ship also eventually gets another passage of a cassette player. Faye returned to the ship and, rather than pay Jet the delivery fee, she walked away but still sneaked a look from around the corner. It was a tape she herself recorded in her youth.[2] None of the images on the video are familiar to her, hence she spent several nights viewing the contents of the tape. Eventually, a half asleep Ed, reveals that she might know where the area the video was recorded. She rigs the ship to go to Earth, straps Ed to her ship, and takes off. They finally find it and, once there, Faye is approached by an elderly woman who turns out to be an ex-classmate, Sally Yung. She starts to explain some details about Faye but she runs away instead, back to the Bebop. Later, during a shower, her memory resurfaces and she decides she has to leave for good, to where she belongs. However, when she finally finds the area of her home, she only finds a pile of rubble where her home used to be. Resigned, Faye tracks the perimeter of what once was her bed on the ground and lies down in the light of the sunset.[4]\r\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/personality.txt:66:Frustrated and upset by the absence of her roots, Faye went back to her ship when she notices a car driving by in pursuit of another. The driver is Julia, and Faye immediately shoots out the tires of her attacker, saving her. She gets in the car and they escape for a while. Faye offers to team up, but Julia says she's looking for someone. They return to the spaceport and Julia reveals she knows Faye knows Spike by asking her to tell him she'll be waiting \"there.\" Surprised, she goes back to the Bebop and, albeit hesitantly, delivers the message to Spike. After he leaves, Faye wondered aloud to Jet why Spike wants to risk his life with Julia, and both are anxious not to see him again.[10]\r\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:17:  status: delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:20:  delivered_at: \"2026-05-30T06:05:00+08:00\"\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:22:  # 2026-05-30 06:05 推送：一次性 cron delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:31:  status: delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:34:  delivered_at: \"2026-05-31T18:03:00+08:00\"\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:35:  # 2026-05-31 18:03 推送：一次性 cron delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:44:  status: delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:47:  delivered_at: \"2026-05-31T18:03:00+08:00\"\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:48:  # 2026-05-31 18:03 推送：一次性 cron delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:117:  │   ├─ \"/递话\"  → 走递话流程（见下方 3.5，我自己处理）\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:246:  → 直接 deliver 给用户（cron 已设好 announce delivery）\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:265:### 3.6 消息转达（/递话）\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:267:跨用户异步带话功能，不涉及 Son/Spirit，我自己处理。\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:284:这样后续递话时就知道用哪个 bot 推送。\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:286:#### 存话 + 递话流程\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:289:触发: 用户说 \"/递话 <对方称呼> <内容>\" 或明确表达让带话的意图\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:303:      名称: deliver-{from_name}-{to_name}\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:307:        message: \"{from_name}托我带话：{内容}\",\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:311:      delivery: {\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:321:  → 等待短暂后，查 cron.get(jobId) 看 delivery 状态\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:450:### 跨 Agent 传话\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/AGENTS.md:558:4. 满足所有条件的：创建一次性 announce cron（delivery.mode=announce, channel=qqbot, accountId=条目中的bot_channel, to=qqbot:c2c:用户sender_id, deleteAfterRun=true）推消息给用户，推完标记 `delivered`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":422,"aggregated":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/personality.txt:41:Faye was born on August 14, 1994 on Earth,[1] presumably in Singapore, as the daughter of rather wealthy parents.[citation needed] As a child, Faye was shy but very positive and outgoing with her friends. She was a cheerleader in high school. One day, along with some friends, she recorded a message on an old Betamax videotape to be delivered ten years in the future as a time capsule.[2]\r\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/personality.txt:62:One day, Faye received a package on the Bebop and, fearing it was from a collector or worse, fled without opening it. Jet was forced to pay the delivery fee and eventually found out it was a Betamax tape. The ship also eventually gets another passage of a cassette player. Faye returned to the ship and, rather than pay Jet the delivery fee, she walked away but still sneaked a look from around the corner. It was a tape she herself recorded in her youth.[2] None of the images on the video are familiar to her, hence she spent several nights viewing the contents of the tape. Eventually, a half asleep Ed, reveals that she might know where the area the video was recorded. She rigs the ship to go to Earth, straps Ed to her ship, and takes off. They finally find it and, once there, Faye is approached by an elderly woman who turns out to be an ex-classmate, Sally Yung. She starts to explain some details about Faye but she runs away instead, back to the Bebop. Later, during a shower, her memory resurfaces and she decides she has to leave for good, to where she belongs. However, when she finally finds the area of her home, she only finds a pile of rubble where her home used to be. Resigned, Faye tracks the perimeter of what once was her bed on the ground and lies down in the light of the sunset.[4]\r\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/personality.txt:66:Frustrated and upset by the absence of her roots, Faye went back to her ship when she notices a car driving by in pursuit of another. The driver is Julia, and Faye immediately shoots out the tires of her attacker, saving her. She gets in the car and they escape for a while. Faye offers to team up, but Julia says she's looking for someone. They return to the spaceport and Julia reveals she knows Faye knows Spike by asking her to tell him she'll be waiting \"there.\" Surprised, she goes back to the Bebop and, albeit hesitantly, delivers the message to Spike. After he leaves, Faye wondered aloud to Jet why Spike wants to risk his life with Julia, and both are anxious not to see him again.[10]\r\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:17:  status: delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:20:  delivered_at: \"2026-05-30T06:05:00+08:00\"\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:22:  # 2026-05-30 06:05 推送：一次性 cron delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:31:  status: delivered\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:34:  delivered_at: \"2026-05-31T18:03:00+08:00\"\n/root/.openclaw/workspace-father/heart/pending_urges.md:35:  # 202